                <summary>The Augusta Medical Society was organized at a meeting of Augusta County
                    physicians on June 26. The group is intended to enhance professional
                    relationships and to standardize procedures for costs and payment during the
                    war. The group elected V. T. Churchman as president unanimously, T. W. Shelton
                    as vice president, W. L. Walters as treasurer, and Samuel Kennerly, Jr., as
                    secretary. Signing a resolution regarding the practice of medicine during the
                    war were these four, plus R. A. McChesney, J. M. Watson, James E. Dunlap, John
                    E. Lockbridge, John C. Hyde, James A. J. Waddell, H. M. Patterson, James T.
                    Clark, B. F. Hopkins, Joseph Wilson, Sr., Isaac Hall, C. A. McCutchen, J. Alex
