                <summary>Major William M. Wilson, commanding the 32nd Regiment of Virginia Militia
                    stationed at Mt. Sidney, announced the orders of the Adjutant General of
                    Virginia that a regimental muster will be held in New Hope, Saturday, July 4.
                    All persons between 18 and 45 who are not already in service in the Confederacy,
                    those who have had substitutes, and those previously exempted for whatever
                    reasons are required to gather, or face repercussions of the law.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look>**</look>
